items.text: Nightmare to get a table after 0830 hrs over weekends
Ah fu xia mian! <3
01-75 blue lagoon western food. Cheap, good, friendly!
The nasi lemak here is awesome very nice !!
Hougang lee Chen fish soup, worth the wait and reasonable price! Aunty friendly too. :)
01-58 Hylam Street Chicken Rice dam nice!! The peanut soup!
#stervylicious #friedcarrotcake - best midweek folks! Had a speciality White fried carrot cake :) it comes with $2/3/4 orders . Heavenly.... Must try - hai sheng carrot cakcake /#01-49....
try Blue lagoon western food , food is good , price is good too .
Try wak LAN mee soup power#01-14
Blue Lagoon Western Food is nice and cheap!!! Definitely recommended!!!
Yummy fish ball noodles, vegetarian beehoon, Nasi lemak and teh.
Chck out these food stalls: Nasi Lema #01-07, Ah Fu Prawn Noodle #01-78, Blue Lagoon western food #01-75, Yong Tau Fu #01-70, Chau Chee Kway Chap #01-67,
Good prawn noodles, teow chew porridge, lor mee etc
Kway chap: What we enjoyed most was their fragrant stew sauce (lor).  Meat was well-cooked. Yum!
Forgot to mention, Xian Jin Mix Vege Stall starts from morning to around 3pm. Usually have long queue between 12pm to 2pm. If health is ya concern, this stall ain't right for u.
Things to try here: carrot cake, "French fries" carrot cake, lor mee, bak Chor mee and wanton mee.
Fishball noodles. Locals make a bee-line for Joo Chiat Chiap Kee #01-31 for handmade fishballs & pork balls. Yummy & bouncy. Noodles are springy ('q') but overall dish was a tad too salty
Rui xing kopi. Best in spore
The soy bean drink also nice too
Sim Kee Duck Rice & Noodle Yummy!
Tasty Teo Chew dishes and Porridge / Rice , stall closed Tue/Thurs
fresh and piping hot nasi lemak from hon ni kitchen
Ah fu xia mian is a musttttt! <3
Shui Huat Nasi Lemak is awesome & cheap! In fact, everything here is cheap 
Chris kway chap!
Chiap Kee Noodles awesome shit. fishball handmade portion small but gd. When kiap fishball beware yur fishball mite just fly off cos its just too smooth and good. Hong Ni kitchen always da best. $2
You must try the vegetarian bee hoon here. Sold between 7am-9am. Also, try the chai tow kway (fried carrot cake) in both the black and white variants. There is also good wanton mee to be had here.
Vegetarian bee Hoon. Bak chor mee. Carrot cake. Kuey chup. Hand made bee Hoon Kuey. Prawn noodle. Nasi lemak. All is must try!!!
The Nasi Biryani at the last stall nearest the Singpost outlet is a must try!
#stervylicious #kwaychap - best day,. Very traditional in taste. the caramel braised ingredients are nicely cooked. Worth trying - Chai Chee Kway Chap /#01-67
Good and cheap mixed veg rice at #01-02. only $2!!!
01-69 kaya toast, try their ice yin yon more  coffee . 3 

Nasi Lemak: Shui Huat #01-35 sees long queues. However, we came on wrong day. (Alrdy cold) fried chicken wing was not edible. BTW Ikan bilis is slightly spicy, if u r ordering for kids who dun like it
Variety of food. So far all the stall is above average
Stall 1-46. The other fish soup stall that is pretty good.
Simple tasty home cooked dishes to go with porridge / rice and reasonably priced
Recommends the nasi lemak which the 2 grandparents are selling. On the same row as the joo chiat fishball noodle.
Sliced fish soup
Super duper yummy fish soup!! Coffee and teh are good too!
Hwa Chong Sliced fish soup #01-65
So in love with the lor mee here!!! 137 lor mee.. Must try! 
Teo Chew rice/porridge has nice home cooked taste and reasonably priced will come again
Try the Sempurna Jaya Malay rice. Good taste and reasonably priced.
Must try He Xing Yong Tau Foo!!! Beware of the waiting time!
Teh halia panas!!
Lots of vegetarian stores here
Good food, damn shiok :)
01-134 vegetables stall nice fresh vege, nice friendly staff
Try shui Huat Nasi Lemak... Cheap n good... any 3 dishes for $2
Wanton mee stall at #01-37 is horrible. Not only did they get the order wrong but the lady in rude as well. As for quality of mee, go figure.
Guay chap is nice but少了我爱的猪肚就......so so le:(
Best Ban Mian at 1-68!
Please avoid fruit juice store #01-63 at all cost. The drinks are very diluted and the uncle adds syrup to make up for the sweetness.
#stervylucious #lormee - best Mid week :) ordered Lor Mee today :) must say , it is quite unique.  POWER!! must try - 137 lor mee/ #01-41.
A must-try for He Xing yong tau foo!! Plenty of variety & at a reasonable price
Carrot cake...Hai Sheng
Been a long timeeeee
kim seng fresh fruit 01-184 great variety. Sweet oranges, crunchy apples, really nice grapes ...
Prata: Nur Indah Kitchen #01-11 looks like they had lots of press coverage b4. Tried their plain prata on a busy Sunday morning. Limp & hard :-( & their std curry was weak/diluted
The vegetarian store at 01-34  rocks.  Try the porridge with gingko nuts.
#stervylicious #kwaychap - best day.  Very traditional in taste n style. The kway is generous .. the caramel braised ingredients are nicely cooked. Worth trying - Chai Chee Kway Chap /#01-67
Wantan mee: There r 3 stalls: A) #01-47 B) #01-45 & C) #01-01. As a complete package, B tasted d best. But C has more traditional char siew & wantans, lotsa vege (they lost pts on overcooked noodles)
01-166 fish here may be pricier but fresher than other stalls. And stall owner willing to pack the fish how you want it
Chilli is Power. Soup is Cantonese home made soup. Must try transparent chicken feet with Thai sauce.
The Malay food @ Sempurna Jaya. Tasty and good value for money.
Thumbs up as usual for 朝洲菜饭小抄 stall, they serve excellent home cooked dishes and reasonable prices
Nice and cheap @ #01-02 ($2 for one bak kut teh & $2 for any 3 types of dishes and rice) 
Chck out the prawn noodle soup, kuay chap, pork porridge #01-27, fish soup, Nasi lema, coffee, western food, wantan noodle, etc. Note: This is a morning market.
Yummy carrot cake (black) #01-70
fruit owner has nice red apples, and sometimes organic grapes, seasonal, first come first serve
Melts in your mouth
Xian Jin mixed vegetable rice #01-02 three dishes + rice only $2! Tasty and cheap :) they also sell bak kut teh for $2 too!
01-173 meat stall get my fresh pork here
$2 for 什菜饭at #01-02
Good food
Try Chris Kway Chap #01-80, Porridge at #01-27
Store 01-33 干板面好吃
宣均 Xian Jin Mix Vege Stall "01-02". S$2 as standard pricing. Cheap n good. Worth trying out. They also got Ba Kut Teh.
Chris Kway Chap is the best. Worth my 30mins spent at the HDB Carpark.
Prepare to queue up for their drinks
Famous Sungei Road Trishaw LAKSA #01-59... Thick and nice gravy
The foods here are so nice. too many foods to choose from.. but im hungry
Try to come here before 1pm because most of the stalls close/sell out at that time.
Chris kuay chup! Try it!
Bak chor mee. Chai Chee Minced Meat Noodle #01-64 sells it soup-only. It  is a very Bedok phenomena ;-)
群芳豆花水 (Koon Fong Soyabean) #01-03. They have some unique stuff like self made jelly n dessert. Their soya drink serving is larger than usual @ low price. Worth checking it out. Usually closes on wed.
01-89 chicken stall friendly customer service
Laska is nice
Hougang Lee Chen Cooked Food long queue! Seems like very nice!
Bee Chun Cafe 01-73 .try the Kaya
Store 01-37 , try their jiao zi n dumplings .
Very nice "soon ban"... 01-76 stall
#01-55 mus try the chai chee carrot cake
Love dishes @ this stall , thumbs up must try
Coffee, coffee, coffee..
Try the Prata here it's very good! But the aunty is abit grumpy..
Blue Lagoon Western Food (opens till 8:30pm, Monday closed, sometimes closed on Thursday and Friday)
Vegetarian? 3 options for vegetarians here. But they only operate in the morning.  Look at pics ;) Bon appetite!
Joo chiat chip kee #01-31  the noodle nice. Cheap, onli $2.50 and the fish ball got alot. Worth it ar. Haha.
Hon ni kitchen best Nasi lemak !
Some more: Chai Chee minced meat noodle #01-64, Wanton noodle #01-47, Fish soup #01-46, Vegetarian fried bee hoon #01-44, Rui Xing Coffee #01-42
The best stall here is the vegetarian beehoon (get the mee/beehoon mix)Honorable mentions: white chai tow kway from Hai Sheng, wonton mee, hum chim pang
Great Ban Mian at stall 1-68. Freshly made noodles on the spot.
Must come "阿丽怡包河粉" stall to eat!! Their fried dumplingss and ipoh hor fun is really awesomeeee!! U will definately regret if u don't try it!! :D
Chai Chee Kway Chap very good. Not salty, Kway is soft.  Chili is the right one.
离家最近的小贩中心，因为近所以却总是忽略他的味道~在这里可以用很低的价格买到好吃的食物~所以新加坡真是个好地方，无论消费高低都有好东西吃，而且不用担心会吃到毒化物。。。推荐这里的斋米粉，2刀，撑到你扶墙走~
Penang fried kway teow
#stervylicious #meepok. - had a great brekky. If you are still not filled, have a delicious deep fried dough with kopi-o like me. Gotta try it - rem order soup based - #01-31/joo chiat chiap Kee.
Veggie rice beside the bwa kwa stall(New Eastern) is the best!
